title: Angela Zhao
text:
Angela Zhao is a first year PhD student in Biostatistics at Johns Hopkins University. Previously, she completed her ScM in Biostatistics from Johns Hopkins University (2024) and her Joint BS in Computer Science and Biology with a Minor in Maths from McGill University (2022).
Her research interests are mainly in methods of analyzing time-series data, including stochastic modeling, neural networks, and functional data analysis. Domain-specific application interests include wearable device and imaging data.
Hobbies include bouldering, investing, stand-up comedy, and playing classical music (fun fact: she previously taught piano for 4 years).
